						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">SoleGooseProductions wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Perhaps, then, my question should be: how can/should one load sections of columns?<br /></div>&quot;Sections&quot; ?<br /><br />Currently, the code starting at &quot;DrawColumn&quot; and though the end is what uploads 30 bytes, adding a new 1x30 tile area on screen (or 8x240 pixels). Each time you call DrawNewColumn it calculates the source pointer, destination pointer, and then uploads those 30 bytes.<br /><br />As you noticed, it's the &quot;scroll&quot; variable that chooses which of the 256 columns to upload. &quot;DrawColumn&quot; doesn't modify &quot;scroll&quot;, only reads it.<br /><br />So now you just need to figure out how you want to modify &quot;scroll&quot; before you call &quot;DrawColumn&quot;.<br /><br />Does this make sense?</div>

